### Fields value automatically generated

Some CDL fields value will be automatically generated if they are not set manually during the push.

These fields are:

- application.componentId (website domain: window.location.hostname )
- page.hierarchy (\['unknown'\])
- page.title (document.title)
- page.url (window.location.href)
- page.referrerUrl (document.referrer)
- page.instanceId (unique identifier with the format 'TIMESTAMP-RANDOMVALUES'. Example: '1710318932652-kfGPylhjewk2ZRxeeBRRmd20')
- page.previousInstanceId (unique identifier with the format 'TIMESTAMP-RANDOMVALUES'. Example: '1710318932652-kfGPylhjewk2ZRxeeBRRmd19')
- user.viewportSize (Ex: 1826x878)
- user.userAgent (navigator.userAgent)
- user.screenResolution (Ex: 1920x1080)

Additional fields **only** if the push contains `eventProperties` object:

- eventProperties.utcTimestamp (number of milliseconds since the Unix Epoch)
- eventProperties.timezoneOffset (the difference, in minutes, between a date as evaluated in the UTC time zone, and the same date as evaluated in the local time zone)
- eventProperties.eventId (unique identifier with the format 'TIMESTAMP-RANDOMVALUES'. Example: '1710318932652-kfGPylhjewk2ZRxeeBRRmd20')
